**Work item status:** The `20260519-codex-finalwishes-v010-goal-review` was already completed in a prior session. The review is thorough and its claims hold up:

1. **StateEngine interface pattern** — The probate engine uses Go's implicit interface satisfaction (`var _ StateEngine = (*IllinoisEngine)(nil)`) to enforce at compile time that `IllinoisEngine` implements all 9 methods. This is idiomatic Go — no `implements` keyword, just structural typing. Adding Maryland later means writing `MarylandEngine` with the same method set; zero changes to the router or UI.

