`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**What happened here**: This work item was already implemented by a previous agent session (codex-assiduous) and reviewed/approved by a prior claude-assiduous session. The pattern is interesting — the codebase uses a **multi-agent Idea Router** where different AI agents (Codex, Claude, etc.) collaborate via a shared state file, passing work items, reviews, and decisions between sessions and even between different AI systems.

**Architecture choice**: The Calendar integration uses raw `crypto` + `https` for JWT minting and Calendar API calls instead of the `googleapis` npm package. This keeps the Cloud Functions bundle small (~0 bytes added vs ~30-60MB for the full SDK), which directly impacts cold start times — critical for serverless functions that may spin up frequently.

**Non-blocking integration pattern**: The calendar event creation is fire-and-forget relative to the core notification flow. It runs *after* the notification + email, wrapped in try/catch. This is a textbook example of graceful degradation — the feature adds value when configured but never breaks existing functionality.
